<% content_for :title, "Acceptable Use Policy" %>

<article class="prose-legal">
  <h1>Acceptable Use Policy</h1>
  <p class="doc-meta">Effective date: June 1, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Veridion Studios Ltd.</p>

  <p>This policy defines what you may and may not do on the Tessera platform. Violations may result in immediate suspension or permanent termination of your account.</p>

  <h2>1. Permitted use</h2>
  <p>Tessera is for legitimate software development engagements between verified individuals and organisations. You may use the platform to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Post project requests for software development work.</li>
    <li>Offer your software development services as a verified developer.</li>
    <li>Communicate with counterparties about active or potential projects.</li>
    <li>Manage milestone deliverables and associated payments.</li>
    <li>Use invoicing and subscription tools for client billing.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Prohibited conduct</h2>
  <h3>Fee circumvention</h3>
  <p>You may not solicit or accept payment outside the Tessera platform for work that originated as a Tessera project. If you wish to continue a relationship off-platform after a project completes, you must do so after the project is formally closed and a minimum 6-month cooldown period has passed.</p>

  <h3>Fraud and misrepresentation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Misrepresenting your identity, qualifications, or past work.</li>
    <li>Submitting AI-generated portfolio work as your own original work.</li>
    <li>Creating fake reviews, testimonials, or project records.</li>
    <li>Impersonating another user or a Tessera employee.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Harmful content and behaviour</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Uploading malware, exploits, or any code intended to harm users or systems.</li>
    <li>Harassment, threats, hate speech, or discriminatory conduct toward other users.</li>
    <li>Sharing another user's personal information without their consent (doxxing).</li>
    <li>Attempting to access accounts, systems, or data that are not yours.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Illegal activity</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Using the platform for money laundering or sanctions evasion.</li>
    <li>Soliciting or providing services that violate applicable laws.</li>
    <li>Any use that violates export control regulations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Platform abuse</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Automated scraping, crawling, or bulk downloading of platform data.</li>
    <li>Creating accounts via bots or automated means.</li>
    <li>Sending unsolicited messages or spam to other users.</li>
    <li>Attempting to manipulate search rankings, ratings, or visibility.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Reporting violations</h2>
  <p>If you encounter behaviour that violates this policy, please report it to <strong>trust@veridion.studio</strong> with as much detail as possible. We take all reports seriously and investigate them confidentially.</p>

  <h2>4. Enforcement</h2>
  <p>Tessera reserves the right to remove content, suspend, or permanently ban any account that violates this policy. We may also refer matters to law enforcement where appropriate. Our decisions are final.</p>
</article>